anyway, today is inauguration day. we made it. we finally, finally made it. holy shit.

admittedly this is easier said than done, especially when you've developed a habit of shoving all the Bad Stuff down, but negative feelings are just as normal as positive feelings. they're part of being human. you can't shut them out without consequences.

it's a lot to unlearn.

it's also distressing as hell to see this exact same sort of thing happen to giant groups of impressionable people en masse. hello, suppressing negative emotions is bad for you! we need outlets! you're allowed to feel sad! people who give you shit for feeling sad aren't worth it!

it's a weird thing to wrap my mind around because that was the environment I grew up in, not being allowed to show sadness or other negative things. I learnt to bottle everything up. no one wanted to hear it. it's nice to finally have a label for it??

LRT toxic positivity is something my therapist brought up with me during one of our sessions. for as much progress as we've made wrt mental health, social media often cultivates toxic spaces like this which disregard others' struggles or pins negative emotions as 'not allowed'
